# Agent Instructions

This project is an ASP.NET Minimal API integration component using Dapr pub/sub with the in-memory component. It exposes `POST /publish`, and the subscribed endpoint runs the order send pipeline, writing the result to a local storage binding.

## Project overview

- Framework: .NET 10
- App type: ASP.NET Core Minimal API
- Dapr package: `Dapr.AspNetCore`
- App id: `{{ .appId }}`
- App port: `5001`
- Pub/sub component: `pubsub` (in-memory)
- Topic: `messages`
- Output binding: `local-storage` (Dapr local storage, rootPath `./local/test/out`)

## Important files

- `src/Program.cs` - DI wiring and framework registration.
- `src/Configuration/Constants.cs` - component, topic, and binding names.
- `src/Ingest/Endpoints.cs` - HTTP endpoints and the Dapr subscription.
- `src/Process/` - the order send pipeline, its builder, and step classes.
- `local/dapr-components/` - local Dapr component YAMLs (pub/sub, storage binding).
- `src/{{ .name }}.http` - sample HTTP requests.

## Build and run

Build:

```bash
dotnet build ./src
```

Run with Dapr:

```bash
dapr run \
  --app-id {{ .appId }} \
  --app-port 5001 \
  --dapr-http-port 3500 \
  --resources-path ./local/dapr-components \
  -- dotnet run --project ./src --urls http://localhost:5001
```

## Testing

Use `src/{{ .name }}.http` to post a sample message to `POST /publish`.

## Framework guidance

How-to knowledge for the Intropy framework (pipelines, blocks, endpoints, Dapr components, testing) lives in the Intropy skills collection under `.agents/skills/`. If it is not installed, run `intropy skills collection add --name intropy --ref harbor.intropy.io/skills/index:latest`.
